RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAND MACALLAN tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, began a bid while saving ground around the turn and dueled down the lane to just hold the win. CAJUN OCCASION raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, began a bid from the three path coming around the bend and dueled to the wire, narrowly missing. CRUISING DEREK led the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way from the two path coming around the turn, was caught in upper stretch and chased the top two home from there. ALTAIR veered out leaving the gate, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the four path and finished evenly. ROLLERCOASTER MAN stalked the pace setter on the outside early, came around the bend in the three path and weakened in the lane. PERSONAL FINANCE chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began to drop back while racing in the two path around the turn and tired further in the stretch. GOD GIVEN RIGHTS was pinched back leaving the gate, trailed the field throughout, raced in the two path and was never a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Altair
ENTRY.OWNER: Blazing Meadows Farm LLC and Szegi Kerri

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOXGLOVE trailed the field from the three path around the first turn and up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the far turn, gained ground outside and pulled clear. TIMELESS GLORY saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path, dueled in upper stretch and kept on to the wire. GIRL PRO raced in the three path around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, kicked clear while saving ground around the second bend and was caught late. TOOLEGITTOQUIT raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening half mile, came around the far turn in the three path and finished evenly. TIZ LOTTIE raced in the three path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the two path and was outkicked in the lane. BELLSWILLBERINGING raced in the four path around the first turn, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far turn and weakened in the stretch. LADY WOOD stalked the leader on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the two path and faded from there. ASPROPODIA saved ground around the first turn, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the two path and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 65. Claiming Purse 22500. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since November 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered) (Condition Eligibility). RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUPER CARO saved ground around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the rail approaching the quarter pole, kicked clear in upper stretch and held off a late closer to the wire. BODE'S HERITAGE raced in the three path early, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, began a bid from the four path coming around the far bend and gained ground late. IMPERIOUSLY brushed lightly with the horse to her inside leaving the gate, raced in the two path around the first turn, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the far turn and kept on to the finish. PEEP'S DAY saved ground around the first turn, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the far bend and weakened in the final furlong. LUCKY FREEDOM trailed the field from the two path through the opening half mile, came around the far turn still in the two path and improved position mildly in the lane. SUMMER NITRO brushed mildly with the horse to her outside at the start, raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, began a bid from the five path coming around the turn and flattened out in the lane. LADYNESS raced off the pace in the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend and was empty in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 19500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: R SWIRVIN GIRVIN stumbled leaving the gate, recovered to chase the leader up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the turn and drew off in the lane. FACCIA BELLA raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the three path, began a bid nearing the quarter pole and chased the winner home. STORMIN' AMANDA raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, saved ground around the bend and finished evenly. SONG OF AMERICA led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the turn and weakened in the stretch. NOBLE ATTITUDE bumped with the horse to her inside at the start, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, came around the bend in the two and three path and was never a threat. K D STRONG bumped with the horses to either side leaving the gate, raced off the pace early, saved ground at the back of the pack around the turn and was empty in the lane. HONEY HAULER hit the gate and veered out leaving the gate, causing her rider to lose their stirrups and never recover them, and trailed far back throughout. AN INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE START. UPON REVIEW, IT WAS DETERMINED THAT ALL HORSES HAD A FAIR START AND NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.
